              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="md:w-2/3 p-8">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4">Challenge: Employee Fraud Scheme</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Valley Health Services faced a serious crisis when their regular audit failed to detect a procurement manager who had set up a shell company as a vendor. For over 18 months, this employee approved invoices from their own shell company for supplies that were never delivered.</p>
              
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 mb-4 mt-6">Solution: Advanced Vendor Analysis</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">Within weeks of implementing RedFlag, the system identified:</p>
              <ul class="text-gray-600 space-y-2 mb-4 list-disc pl-5">
                <li>Suspicious patterns in a new vendor's billing history</li>
                <li>Connections between employee and vendor information</li>
                <li>Lack of competitive pricing compared to industry standards</li>
                <li>Unusual approval patterns circumventing standard controls</li>
              </ul>
              
              <p class="text-gray-600 italic mt-6">"The reputational damage could have been devastating. RedFlag detected what our standard controls missed completely. Beyond the financial recovery, the peace of mind knowing we have this layer of protection is invaluable." <span class="font-bold">- Michael Rivera, CEO</span></p>
            </div>
          </div>
